Key Match Events: Jayson Tatum's buzzer-beating three-pointer gave Boston a 126-123 win
RJ Barrett recorded his first triple-double in the NBA
Jakob Poeltl scored a career-high 35 points
Post-Match Reflections: The Celtics improved to 11-3 as they begin their championship defense
The Raptors have struggled to close out games throughout the start of their 2024-25 campaign, sitting in last place in the Eastern Conference standings with a 2-12 record
Miscellaneous Highlights: The NBA's Last Two Minute Report revealed several incorrect calls, including one on the final shot of the game where Tatum traveled during his shot
Davion Mitchell should have been whistled for a foul on Jaylen Brown prior to Tatum's shot
Others: Jayson Tatum finished with 24 points, 11 rebounds and nine assists
Jaylen Brown led the team with 27 points, dishing out seven assists of his own
RJ Barrett recorded 25 points and 15 assists in addition to 10 rebounds
